  <Placemark>
    <name>Ramirez Hall</name>
    <description><![CDATA[Corner of Portscheller Street and Main Plaza, Roma.<br/><br/><b>Address:</b> Portsheller Street on Main Plaza, Roma<br/><br/><b>Marker Text:</b> Commercial structure with family home upstairs. On site bought 1872 by Lino Ramirez. Built by architect Heinrich Portscheller (1840-1915), who personally laid brick in fine detail around windows and doors. Three generations of Ramirez family occupied hall.]]></description>
    <Point><coordinates>-99.01851,26.405502,0</coordinates></Point>
  </Placemark>
  <Placemark>
    <name>Robert E. Lee House</name>
    <description><![CDATA[Rio Grande City C.I.S.D. campus off US 83. Also known as Commandant's House.<br/><br/><b>Address:</b> Lee Circle, Rio Grande City<br/><br/><b>Marker Text:</b> Overlooked steamboat dock on Rio Grande, landscape of northern Mexico. Main rooms were walled with military maps of this locality. Used as field quarters by Col. Robert E. Lee, U.S. Army Commandant in Texas, 1860. Recorded Texas Historic Landmark - 1965]]></description>
    <Point><coordinates>-98.808789,26.374025,0</coordinates></Point>
  </Placemark>
